1
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:40,433
<i>You know what,
I've seen her face before.</i>

2
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,600
<i> It's confirmed, Felma.</i>

3
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:42,800
<i> Look at this!</i>

4
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,400
<i> It's in Saudi Arabia.</i>

5
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,567
<i>Yes, that's Hazel's
best friend.</i>

6
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:50,633
<i>Don't tell your mom that
my mom knows what she did.</i>

7
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,400
<i>I will get more furious with you
if you do.</i>

8
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:53,733
<i> What's the problem?</i>

9
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:55,233
<i> You are my problem.</i>

10
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,000
<i> Spy cameras?</i>

11
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:58,067
<i> What for?</i>

12
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,100
<i> For Felma's house.</i>

13
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:03,067
<i>I want my eyes and ears
inside their walls.</i>

14
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,133
<i>Miss Hazel, what are
you doing over there?</i>

15
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,933
<i> I dropped my earring.</i>

16
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,433
<i> Have some snacks.</i>

17
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,767
<i> This iced tea is good.</i>

18
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,233
<i>- This is a laxative, isn't it?
- Yes, Didang.</i>

19
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:16,033
<i>I'm just giving her
a dose of her own medicine.</i>

20
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:19,533
<i>Tell them what you did
to the people at Luntian Park.</i>

21
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,900
<i> I have nothing to confess!</i>

22
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,800
<i> Stop fake crying!</i>

23
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:31,067
<i>You dragged a lot of people
into this!</i>

24
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,300
<i> A lot of people got hurt!</i>

25
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:36,500
<i> My family!</i>

26
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:39,233
<i> The victims at Luntian Park!</i>

27
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:43,400
<i>Even my staff at FMP,
you monster!</i>

28
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:45,267
<i>- You beast!
- Felma!</i>

29
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:49,700
- I will sue you!
- Mom!

30
00:01:49,833 --> 00:01:51,300
No, please, I'm begging you.

31
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:52,800
Have mercy on me.

32
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,733
Please don't sue me.

33
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:57,333
Why are you begging?

34
00:01:57,467 --> 00:01:59,567
You're backing down?

35
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:02,867
Do you not want Manuel
and Jessica to see you?

36
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,133
They would see your true colors?

37
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:07,533
No.

38
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:09,700
I've changed.

39
00:02:09,833 --> 00:02:11,867
I've changed, Felma.

40
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,167
I don't want to break my promise
to my daughter.

41
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:18,700
I promised Jessica
that I would change.

42
00:02:18,833 --> 00:02:21,233
I'm not capable of what
you're accusing me of.

43
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:25,200
If you believe that I have
something to do

44
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:28,900
with what happened at the park,
then prove it.

45
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:33,067
But if you want me to confess,
you'll just waste your time.

46
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,700
But whatever happens,

47
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:38,200
I will never confess
to something I didn't do.

48
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:39,133
Get out!

49
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:40,433
- Mom! Mom!
- Get out!

50
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:41,200
Mom.

51
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:44,100
Felma, I won't fight with you.

52
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:46,367
I won't fight with you.

53
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,633
I'm done.

54
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,033
I'm tired of fighting,
like I told Jessica,

55
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:51,667
I will change.

56
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,933
I don't want any more trouble.

57
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:54,000
I don't want to fight.

58
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:56,100
So please listen to me.

59
00:02:56,233 --> 00:02:58,100
I'm telling the truth.

60
00:02:58,233 --> 00:02:59,100
Let's stop this.

61
00:03:01,467 --> 00:03:02,133
- Ma'am Felma.
- Mom.

62
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:04,733
Ma'am Felma, don't.

63
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:07,333
Just let her leave.

64
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:11,633
She won't confess to anything
even if we gang up on her.

65
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,233
Oh, my!

66
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:16,867
I should have slapped
her face, too!

67
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,333
Pull her hair out!

68
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:19,467
She's been getting on my nerves!

69
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,967
My gosh!

70
00:03:21,133 --> 00:03:22,600
I will smack her next time!

71
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:24,767
Mom, please calm down.

72
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:26,767
Just let her be.

73
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:28,733
We've gotten our revenge.

74
00:03:33,433 --> 00:03:34,967
We did?

75
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:39,500
I only gave her a taste
of her own medicine.

76
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:41,633
What did you do to Hazel?

77
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:02,667
My gosh, I had to go places to
look for ice to put on my face.

78
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,033
What a wasted effort.

79
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:09,400
I tried so hard not to fight
back while Felma was hitting me.

80
00:04:09,533 --> 00:04:11,833
But Manuel and Jessica
didn't show up.

81
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:12,900
If I knew they wouldn't
be there,

82
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:15,700
I would have smacked
that woman's face!

83
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:16,900
<i> I'm scared, Hazel.</i>

84
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:21,467
<i>Paz said that Felma
is going to sue us.</i>

85
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,500
And you believe that witch?

86
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,100
That video has no bearing.

87
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:27,333
It won't hold up in court.

88
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:30,967
Don't worry.

89
00:04:37,167 --> 00:04:38,800
My stomach hurts.

90
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:40,833
I think I'm having
stomach cramps.

91
00:04:40,967 --> 00:04:42,200
What did I eat?

92
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:48,067
<i> This iced tea is good.</i>

93
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,633
<i>You can really taste the tea...</i>

94
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:50,367
<i> It stands out.</i>

95
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,100
<i> Where did you buy this?</i>

96
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:53,667
<i> That's my own blend.</i>

97
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,667
<i> Especially made for you.</i>

98
00:04:57,767 --> 00:05:00,400
That little brat!

99
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,800
Coleen.

100
00:05:02,967 --> 00:05:04,433
Okay, bye. I have to go.

101
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:08,200
Miss.

102
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,467
Miss.

103
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,033
Where's the closest bathroom
around here?

104
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:15,700
Try the eatery,
the one on that corner.

105
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,500
- That way?
- Yes.

106
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:18,567
Thank you.

107
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,833
Did she hurt you?

108
00:05:30,967 --> 00:05:32,267
No, Sir.

109
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,733
My gosh, she can't
stand up to Miss Felma.

110
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,167
She's full of drama.

111
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:39,367
In the end, she's the
one who ends up hurt.

112
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,900
My mom didn't fight back?

113
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,867
Why, Jessica?

114
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,500
Do you want your mom
to fight back

115
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:48,967
after everything she did?

116
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:52,167
The nerve of her
if she fights back.

117
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:53,733
Coleen, sweetie.

118
00:05:55,767 --> 00:06:01,000
Felma, next time, don't let
Hazel come inside the house.

119
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:03,100
I already had her banned.

120
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:10,700
Excuse me.

121
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:20,033
Mom, why did you come here?

122
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:21,233
If you like to visit us,

123
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:23,867
we could meet you outside,
not here.

124
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,867
You made Auntie Felma mad.

125
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,367
<i>Sweetie, you're still
taking their side.</i>

126
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:31,500
Mom, why do you sound like that?

127
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:32,900
Are you okay?

128
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:40,167
Sweetie, I'm in the hospital.

129
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:45,033
<i>I suffered severe diarrhea
and cramping.</i>

130
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,033
<i> What?</i>

131
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:47,167
<i> What happened?</i>

132
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,500
<i> Mom, are you okay?</i>

133
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:52,133
<i>I had a massive intake
of laxative.</i>

134
00:06:52,267 --> 00:06:55,300
<i> I almost got dehydrated.</i>

135
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:58,067
I thought I was going
to collapse.

136
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,533
I'm glad someone brought me
to the hospital.

137
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,300
If not, I could have died.

138
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:05,233
<i> You had a laxative?</i>

139
00:07:05,367 --> 00:07:10,767
<i>So it was true, you and
Aunt Alice had laxatives.</i>

140
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:13,700
<i>You put it in the sisig
they served at the park.</i>

141
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:16,700
No, Sweetie.

142
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:20,933
Don't believe that,
don't believe what they say.

143
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:23,567
Coleen did this to me.

144
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,533
She put a laxative in my drink.

145
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:27,567
No, Mom.

146
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,967
Coleen won't do that.

147
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,567
<i> But she did.</i>

148
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,567
She wants to get back at me

149
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:36,033
for those baseless accusations
against me.

150
00:07:36,167 --> 00:07:37,800
But, Sweetie...

151
00:07:37,933 --> 00:07:42,267
I swear, I'm innocent.

152
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,867
I have nothing to do with it.

153
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:49,133
Sweetie, I've changed
for your sake.

154
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,533
<i> Mom.</i>

155
00:07:50,667 --> 00:07:52,467
Mom, get well soon.

156
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,667
Who are you talking to?

157
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,767
Your lying mother?

158
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,700
What are you two talking about?

159
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:05,433
Is it true?

160
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:07,667
Is it true, Coleen?

161
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:11,033
You put a laxative
in my mom's drink?

162
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:18,800
Answer me!

163
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:23,267
Let go of me!

164
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:25,433
Answer me first!

165
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:27,133
Don't you ever yell at me!

166
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:28,367
I'm still your big sister!

167
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:32,133
-I said, did you put a laxative?
-Yes, I put a laxative!

168
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:34,233
Happy now?

169
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:38,300
I didn't know you
were this mean.

170
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:39,567
Me?

171
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,433
Hello? Your mom was the one
being bad,

172
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:43,233
so I'm just teaching her
a lesson!

173
00:08:45,267 --> 00:08:47,533
She's in the ER right now,
almost dehydrated.

174
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,533
You could have killed her!

175
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:50,767
Wow!

176
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,200
You're exaggerating!

177
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,333
Hello, I only put three bags!

178
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,767
Not the whole box!

179
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,233
That's too much!

180
00:08:58,367 --> 00:09:00,533
You think it's a joke?

181
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:01,800
What about your mom?

182
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:04,733
She put a laxative in the sisig
they served

183
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:06,267
at the feeding program.

184
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:09,733
You don't have proof
that my mom did it.

185
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:11,000
Wow!

186
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:13,133
So you're taking her side now?

187
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:18,067
Let go of me or else...

188
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,033
Or else what?

189
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,667
What are you going to do?

190
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:21,467
Or else, I'll do this!

191
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:26,500
You're mean!

192
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:28,100
Come here!

193
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:29,767
You don't want to stop?

194
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,233
Did you think I wouldn't
fight back?

195
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:32,300
Because you're so mean!

196
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,133
How could you do that?

197
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,433
Your mom deserves it!

198
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:39,367
No!

199
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:40,333
Stop it!

200
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:42,300
My mom is in the hospital
because of you!

201
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:44,067
Jessica! Jessica, stop it!

202
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,700
- Coleen!
- Wait!

203
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,533
- Coleen poisoned my mom!
- Coleen!

204
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:48,667
- Wait!
- Coleen!

205
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,700
Mommy is in the hospital

206
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:51,333
- because of you!
- I said knock it off!

207
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:53,333
Perhaps you've forgotten
that I got hospitalized too

208
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,267
because of her.

209
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,500
You were hospitalized, too!

210
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:57,433
And now you're taking her side?

211
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:59,067
Jessica!

212
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,100
Jessica, knock it off!

213
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:01,667
Wait!

214
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,967
- Jessica!
- Hey, what's going on?

215
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,533
You're fighting
in front of your parents!

216
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,467
Jessica, come here!

217
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,567
Jessica, come here!

218
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:11,000
Stop it!

219
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:11,867
What is going on?

220
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:17,000
Coleen, we have to talk.

221
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,267
Come here!

222
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:31,767
Coleen, why did you do that
to Jessica?

223
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:34,900
She's still recovering
from the accident.

224
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,967
Didn't that occur to you?

225
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,267
Mom, I just can't hold it
anymore.

226
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,967
She's siding with her mom.

227
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:44,800
Because you did something wrong.

228
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:47,767
So, you're siding with her, too?

229
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,600
Dad, I just defended mom.

230
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:53,667
She's seriously ill right now.

231
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,533
Sweetie, is she telling
the truth?

232
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:58,600
Hazel could have just made it up
to make you feel bad for her

233
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:00,467
and make Coleen look bad.

234
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:04,000
Dad, I saw mommy's condition
through a video call.

235
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:11,200
Wait, are you siding
with Coleen?

236
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:13,000
No, sweetie.

237
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:15,033
I'm not taking anyone's side.

238
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:17,167
Are you sure?

239
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,133
Because when Jessica
got hospitalized,

240
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:21,300
you've been so close to her.

241
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:24,133
You only care about her.

242
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,967
Sweetie, that's not true, okay?

243
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,400
You know me.

244
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:31,033
Are you jealous of Jessica?

245
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:33,267
Is that why you're
picking a fight with her?

246
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,133
No, Mom!

247
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:38,100
Why would I get jealous of her?

248
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:40,333
She started the fight, Mom.

249
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:43,833
She got mad at me for
getting back at her mom!

250
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,467
You don't have to
take revenge for me.

251
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,367
We're mad at Hazel, right?

252
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,900
Because of the wrong
things she did?

253
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:52,567
And now you're going
to do the same thing?

254
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:54,600
Apologize to Jessica.

255
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:56,100
What?

256
00:11:56,233 --> 00:11:56,867
No way!

257
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,433
I'm not going to apologize!

258
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:02,767
Sweetie, you're at fault too!

259
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,133
And Coleen is older than you.

260
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:06,167
You're supposed to respect her.

261
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:09,100
And sweetie, she's the only one
who really accepts you

262
00:12:09,233 --> 00:12:11,367
as her sibling.

263
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:14,767
Dad, so I should just
let her hurt Mom?

264
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:19,000
I know that Mom has
been hurting people.

265
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:21,300
I know she's gone too far.

266
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:26,200
But Dad, Mom's hurt too.

267
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:28,200
She's just trying
to win us back,

268
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:31,767
and I admit I still have
resentment toward her.

269
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:34,300
But, Dad, she's still my mom.

270
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:36,267
Sweetie.

271
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:39,533
You know what, Sweetie,
I understand how you feel.

272
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:41,800
I don't want you to lose
your love and respect

273
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:43,600
for your mom.

274
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:45,700
But not to the point where
you have to get into fights

275
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,900
just to defend her.

276
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:49,267
Go on, Sweetie.

277
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,833
Apologize to Coleen.

278
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,567
I said, apologize to Jessica!

279
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,033
I don't want to!

280
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:12,367
You're not going to apologize
to each other?

281
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,233
Don't test our patience.

282
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:19,267
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

283
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:33,533
Did you see that?

284
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:40,500
When do you think those two
will make up?

285
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,900
Like, a genuine
reconciliation,

286
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:45,067
not like what they showed
earlier.

287
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,933
They were just faking it.

288
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,567
You noticed too.

289
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:50,000
I've gotten used to it.

290
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:55,833
It reminds me of Jeffrey
and Andrea at that age.

291
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,967
They were even worse.

292
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:58,933
Whenever they fought,

293
00:13:59,067 --> 00:14:00,233
I'd make them apologize
to each other.

294
00:14:00,367 --> 00:14:05,667
They'd hug it out, even cry
while saying sorry.

295
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,967
But the moment
I turned my back...

296
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:11,200
They're at it again.

297
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:15,367
Did they still fight a lot
after I left for Saudi Arabia?

298
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,533
Almost every day.

299
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:24,033
And the things they fought over
are totally meaningless stuff.

300
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:27,100
Yeah, like kids.

301
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,300
Hey, do you remember
their shallowest fight?

302
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:30,600
That one...

303
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:34,267
what was it again?
Something about a spoon?

304
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,667
The one where you knocked
the spoon off the table?

305
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:40,633
Then you made them pick it up,
and no one wanted to?

306
00:14:40,767 --> 00:14:41,767
- Right?
- That's right.

307
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:44,300
Then they started
teasing each other.

308
00:14:44,433 --> 00:14:45,933
That's when the fight started.

309
00:14:46,067 --> 00:14:47,400
Yeah. Exactly.

310
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:49,967
They were yelling,
accusing each other,

311
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:53,333
and airing out their grudges.

312
00:14:53,467 --> 00:14:55,333
And when you scolded them...

313
00:14:55,467 --> 00:14:57,033
Oh, they both ran away
at the same time, right?

314
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,400
Without anyone knowing.

315
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:00,100
They didn't know about
each other's plans either.

316
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:02,367
And they were surprised
to see each other, right?

317
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:04,667
- Because of...
- Yes, they both showed up

318
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:08,633
at Abel's and Paz's house
at the same time.

319
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:10,167
They were shocked
to see each other.

320
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,767
That they both ran away, right?

321
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:13,567
Oh my gosh.

322
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,300
I miss those days, Felma.

323
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:29,100
I miss Jeffrey and Andrea
so much.

324
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:42,033
I still have things to do
at the office.

325
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:44,967
Paz and I still need
to take care of something.

326
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:13,633
So, that's what happened,

327
00:16:13,767 --> 00:16:15,900
I pulled her hair
all over the place!

328
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:17,933
I smacked her face around!

329
00:16:18,067 --> 00:16:23,000
Felma, I was so furious with
Alice, I really beat her up!

330
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:24,567
I have it on video, wait.

331
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,100
Here, Rose sent this to me.

332
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,567
Really? There's nothing
to confess?

333
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,167
I have nothing to confess!

334
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,800
Even if you beat me up all day.

335
00:16:37,233 --> 00:16:38,367
Oh, really?

336
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,067
What is that?

337
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,500
She's so ugly, right?

338
00:16:45,633 --> 00:16:47,000
Poor woman.

339
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:49,567
What we did was wrong.

340
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:55,600
Hey, after you smack Hazel
not once, not twice,

341
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:59,833
but several times, you're going
to start lecturing me?

342
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:00,933
I know.

343
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:04,467
We're letting our anger
get the better of us.

344
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,267
They deserve it.

345
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:10,633
Because if we don't stand up
to them, they'll eat us alive.

346
00:17:10,767 --> 00:17:12,433
Actually, I'm kind of proud
of Coleen.

347
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:15,567
You know, she's so feisty,
yes girl!

348
00:17:15,733 --> 00:17:17,300
Paz! Oh, come on!

349
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:20,567
Don't condone what
Coleen did, okay?

350
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:21,500
That's not acceptable.

351
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:23,833
I don't like that.

352
00:17:23,967 --> 00:17:25,467
Okay, fine.

353
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:28,567
But, Sis, can you do me a favor?

354
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:30,433
Let's celebrate our
winning moment,

355
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:32,833
just a very light celebration.

356
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:33,933
The video?

357
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:35,133
Yes.

358
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:35,933
Wait here.

359
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:37,200
I'm going to go to the pantry.

360
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,333
I'm going to look
for something to drink.

361
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:41,133
Let's party!

362
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,433
Hazel.

363
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:54,067
I was blacklisted at FMP.

364
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,567
I need a job.

365
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,133
What about Southcrest?

366
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:02,233
No, don't worry.

367
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:07,133
I talked with Miles
before I got discharged.

368
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:11,600
She wants you to email her
your resume.

369
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,267
She will take care of it.

370
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:15,000
Oh my god, is that true?

371
00:18:30,933 --> 00:18:32,233
<i> What?</i>

372
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:33,600
<i>I thought we were
on good terms now?</i>

373
00:18:33,733 --> 00:18:34,767
<i> What is this about?</i>

374
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:39,633
<i>I thought a demon
like you could change.</i>

375
00:18:39,767 --> 00:18:40,967
<i> But I was wrong!</i>

376
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:44,500
<i> You sabotaged my company!</i>

377
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:50,633
I can't believe Felma
and her brat daughter

378
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:53,400
were able to do that to me.

379
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:54,733
And that's your concern?

380
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,933
Don't you think about
the possible lawsuit?

381
00:18:58,067 --> 00:18:59,500
Don't fuss about that.

382
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:02,067
Just relax.

383
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,167
There's nothing in that video

384
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:08,533
that proves we put a laxative
in Felma's product.

385
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:11,033
What we should be thinking
about now

386
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:12,967
is how we are going to get back
at them.

387
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,600
So cold.

388
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:28,567
Felma, look what I found...

389
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:30,200
Hey, what's going on?

390
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,900
Why? Felma!

391
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,633
Roger just called.

392
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:41,500
And he gave me
his notice of resignation.

393
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:45,200
Even the other delivery helpers.

394
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:46,367
They all gave me notice
of resignation.

395
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:49,633
They found a new job.

396
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:51,800
Wait, why?

397
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,633
But you're still paying them

398
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:55,700
even though we've stopped
operations.

399
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:58,267
You're such a kind employer.

400
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,700
They said they're scared,

401
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:06,167
because there's no certainty
about when we'll reopen.

402
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:09,833
They said they have a lot
of dependents to support.

403
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:10,967
And besides...

404
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:16,300
many people are counting
on them.

405
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:17,667
I'm sorry about that.

406
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,133
They have a point.

407
00:20:19,267 --> 00:20:21,467
But I wish they could have
waited a little longer.

408
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,367
Too bad Roger resigned.

409
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:27,433
Roger is our best driver.

410
00:20:27,567 --> 00:20:28,600
Friend...

411
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:32,500
sorry.

412
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:33,700
So that means
there's an opening?

413
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,167
Jeff?

414
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:39,800
- Sweetie.
- Can I apply for the job?

415
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:41,467
Jeffrey.

416
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,067
- Can I?
- Of course.

417
00:20:46,233 --> 00:20:48,400
Wait.

418
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:51,067
Sweetie, is there a problem?

419
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,733
Come on, Mom. You just saw me,

420
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:54,567
and you're asking
if there's a problem.

421
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:58,800
I was checking on Aunt Paz,
asking for updates.

422
00:20:58,933 --> 00:21:02,833
I told her maybe I can help
relieve some of your stress.

423
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:11,933
What you said about...

424
00:21:12,067 --> 00:21:14,667
Are you serious when you said
you're coming back

425
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:18,300
to work at FMP?

426
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,633
Yes, Mom.

427
00:21:20,767 --> 00:21:23,200
But I didn't bring my resume.

428
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,133
Is it okay if I send it later?

429
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:29,567
Stop teasing me.

430
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:32,367
You don't need a resume.

431
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,700
I'm accepting you.

432
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:35,767
I accept you, Sweetie.

433
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,333
You're hired.

434
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:41,233
You know what, Mom,
to be honest,

435
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,800
I've been wanting to come back
here.

436
00:21:43,933 --> 00:21:46,300
But of course, I'm a bit shy
with you.

437
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:48,600
I was stubborn.

438
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:50,567
But you never gave up on me.

439
00:21:53,133 --> 00:21:54,733
You even helped me out.

440
00:21:57,067 --> 00:22:01,800
Mom, about the parcel
and the motorcycle.

441
00:22:03,867 --> 00:22:05,400
Just deduct it from my salary.

442
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:07,700
And then the other...

443
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:12,600
Mom, I'm sorry.

444
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:13,800
I'm sorry.

445
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:38,600
Alice.

446
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:43,400
What's that?

447
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:45,733
Didn't I tell you not to worry?

448
00:22:45,867 --> 00:22:47,400
You're way too paranoid.

449
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,767
That video means nothing.

450
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:52,033
It won't hold up against us.

451
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:53,033
Right, Attorney?

452
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:57,033
Yes.

453
00:22:57,167 --> 00:23:00,033
If that's the only thing
they have against you,

454
00:23:00,167 --> 00:23:01,800
they'll have a hard time.

455
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:04,300
The burden of proof
is with Felma.

456
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:10,567
So, if you believe they
can't find solid evidence,

457
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,067
just deny the accusations.

458
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:15,200
See?

459
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,067
I just need an assurance.

460
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,300
So, are we safe?

461
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:23,300
For now.

462
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:28,167
But we need to be careful.

463
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:32,067
We can't keep attacking them.

464
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,100
Especially you, Mrs. Cruz.

465
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:40,167
That's the reason why you
keep getting in trouble.

466
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:42,167
Excuse me, Attorney.

467
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,133
With all due respect,

468
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:47,367
can you not meddle
with what I'm doing?

469
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,900
I'm not really meddling.

470
00:23:49,033 --> 00:23:50,500
I just want to remind you.

471
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:55,633
Just remember,
silence is your best defense.

472
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:59,133
And besides, if you get
into trouble,

473
00:23:59,267 --> 00:24:01,133
I'm the one you're going
to call anyway.

474
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:09,467
Thank you, I'll go ahead.

475
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,133
I'll walk you out, Attorney.

476
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:15,633
Is that good?

477
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:19,633
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

478
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:27,300
My gosh, your lawyer
talks too much.

479
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:30,267
He's just concerned.

480
00:24:30,433 --> 00:24:33,467
Anyway, I have to get ready
for my job interview.

481
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,767
I'll leave you here for now.

482
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:46,433
Let's see.

483
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:51,933
<i> Don't try our patience.</i>

484
00:24:55,467 --> 00:24:56,433
<i>- Sorry.
- Sorry.</i>

485
00:24:59,067 --> 00:25:02,233
Looks like Coleen and Jessica
are fighting.

486
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,667
Go ahead, you little brat.

487
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,967
Keep fighting with my daughter.

488
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:11,067
To speed up her return to me,
along with her dad.

489
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,167
<i> They both showed up</i>

490
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:15,733
<i>at Abel and Paz's house
at the same time.</i>

491
00:25:15,867 --> 00:25:17,267
<i>They were shocked
to see each other.</i>

492
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:19,633
<i> They both ran away, right?</i>

493
00:25:19,767 --> 00:25:21,233
These shameless people.

494
00:25:21,367 --> 00:25:22,433
And you guys were even laughing.

495
00:25:23,667 --> 00:25:26,200
You managed to reminisce.

496
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:29,300
<i>Paz and I still have things
to take care of.</i>

497
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:35,167
You monsters!

498
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:44,733
Oh, well.

499
00:25:44,867 --> 00:25:46,867
Mom paid off all your debts,
didn't she?

500
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,200
Of course, you'd go back to her.

501
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:49,133
Andrea, I'm drowning.

502
00:25:49,267 --> 00:25:50,600
What should I do?

503
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:51,767
Is it wrong to give up my pride?

504
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:52,867
She's our mother after all.

505
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,000
So what's next?

506
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:55,833
You're going back
to the house, too?

507
00:25:55,967 --> 00:25:57,767
<i> Yes, FMP friends.</i>

508
00:25:57,900 --> 00:26:03,300
<i>We've proven that our factory's
facilities are clean and safe.</i>

509
00:26:03,433 --> 00:26:04,933
They're back in business.

510
00:26:05,067 --> 00:26:07,600
But I'm sure they lost a lot
during the closure.

511
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:10,267
For sure, some of their
customers will be hesitant

512
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:12,100
to eat FMP products again.

513
00:26:12,233 --> 00:26:14,233
So, I still won.

514
00:26:14,367 --> 00:26:16,233
We can eat now.

515
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:17,900
Let's enjoy it, okay?

516
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:18,867
We deserve this.

517
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,200
But don't drink too much.

518
00:26:21,333 --> 00:26:22,400
Mommy Pretty!

519
00:26:22,533 --> 00:26:25,233
Tetay!

520
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:28,200
Jeff, look, we have afritada.

521
00:26:28,333 --> 00:26:30,967
I removed all the fats
and added lots of potatoes.

522
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:32,300
Isn't that how you like it?
